ncy action; decision notice; FONSI; authorization. NFMA forest-plan consistency is addressed: National Forest Management Act; Land Management Plan; Forest Plan; plan consistency. 36 CFR part 219 - Planning is reviewed: 36 CFR part 219; planning; plan components; project consistency. 36 CFR 219.15 project consistency is addressed: 36 CFR 219.15; Land Management Plan; Forest Plan; plan consistency. 36 CFR part 218 - Project-level predecisional administrative review is reviewed: 36 CFR part 218; objection; legal notice; decision notice. Forest Service National Directives portal is reviewed: Forest Service directives; manual; handbook; current directives. Forest Service Region 1 field directives index is reviewed: Region 1 directives; regional supplement; field directives; current directives. FSM 2670 - Threatened, Endangered and Sensitive Plants and Animals is reviewed: FSM 2670; threatened; endangered; sensitive species; biological evaluation. Multiple-Use Sustained-Yield Act, 16 U.S.C. \u00a7\u00a7 528-531 is reviewed: multiple use; sustained yield; outdoor recreation; watershed; wildlife. Organic Administration Act, 16 U.S.C. \u00a7 475 is reviewed: watershed; timber; national forest purposes. Organic Administration Act, 16 U.S.C. \u00a7 551 is reviewed: occupancy; use; protection; national forests. FLPMA Section 206 land-exchange requirements are addressed: Federal Land Policy and Management Act; FLPMA; 43 U.S.C. 1716; Section 206; land exchange; public interest; equal value; cash equalization. Northern Region species of conservation concern page is reviewed: species of conservation concern; Regional Forester; sensitive species; forest plan. 42 U.S.C. \u00a7 4336b - Programmatic environmental documents is reviewed: tiers to; incorporates by reference; programmatic; final environmental impact statement. 42 U.S.C. \u00a7 4336c - Adoption of categorical exclusions is reviewed: categorical exclusion; adopted CE; categorical exclusion path. 42 U.S.C. \u00a7 4336f - Spon